Notes.Text:
This update for net-snmp fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2025-68615: Fixed snmptrapd buffer overflow (bsc#1255491)

Vulnerabilities.Description: net-snmp is a SNMP application library, tools and daemon. Prior to versions 5.9.5 and 5.10.pre2, a specially crafted packet to an net-snmp snmptrapd daemon can cause a buffer overflow and the daemon to crash. This issue has been patched in versions 5.9.5 and 5.10.pre2.
